notesStmt.note: Section of parchment leaves, f. 1-11, are nearly detached; folios 66-67 are completely detached.

msContents.summary: Bound collection of original and copied documents from Ferrara, incomplete at the beginning. The first five folios are notarized copies from the year 1637; followed by three earlier documents (1589, 1518, 1506); chronologically consecutive copies, 1626-1668, and a name index (f. 88r-92r). Several documents are marked with notarial signets, either drawn or stamped.

supportDesc.extent: 99 leaves : 301 x 220 mm. bound to 224 x 230 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Parchment and paper, 99; [ii], 1-8, [i], 9-65, [i], 66-79, [80-95]; near contemporary foliation in ink, upper right recto. Earlier foliation in ink, upper right recto, with many numbers crossed out or partially trimmed away.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by various hands.
